\boxed{\text{War of Attrition}}

Per Baltzer Overgaard analyzed the **War of Attrition** as a signaling game where players compete to demonstrate their resource commitment (e.g., time, effort, or wealth) to convince opponents of their resolve, often in conflicts like territorial disputes or bargaining scenarios. This framework explains why parties may escalate or sustain costly actions to signal strength rather than yield.
